                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12870220" author="ryanobjc" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 23:21:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is that important to change for core code?  If someone is modifying constructors of something like StoreFile, they should Know What They Are Doing, and requiring contributors to use a refactoring-IDE to help them doesn&apos;t seem like an undue requirement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like regionserver code to be easy to understand, but require a lot of thought to change.  The consequences are severe for problems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12870222" author="streamy" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 23:23:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In general I like this pattern (this is similar to the direction the client API went in vs the million method signatures we used to have), but don&apos;t think there&apos;s a need for any wholesale change to this.  I&apos;d be interested to look at things on a case by case basis but agree with Ryan about core code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12870224" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 23:24:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;for core code I am less convinced. But, for example, the HTableDescriptor, HColumnDescriptor, etc constructors, they could be improved. Even for StoreFile, using a builder would make the code easier to &lt;b&gt;read&lt;/b&gt;, and would make these core changes less disruptive to other people building patches on top. (eg just spent 40 minutes or so updating one of my patches after the bloom filter change added some constructor parameters)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12870227" author="streamy" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 23:31:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;agree that HTD and HCD could use come improvement.  Unsure about SF.  Shouldn&apos;t be many of these bigger changes like what blooms had to introduce though I feel your pain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12870254" author="streamy" created="Sat, 22 May 2010 01:04:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s an existing JIRA about builder patterns for client APIs, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2051&quot; title=&quot;Use builder pattern to improve usability of client API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2051&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2051&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917100" author="stack" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 23:37:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not going to be in 0.90, so it looks anyways.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13994724" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 00:39:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not going to happen. Could reopen if there is active interest (aka a patch soon forthcoming)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
